            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>[For] the safety and return and victory of [Gaius] Caesar Augustus, the best princeps, [pontifex] maximus, grandson of the divine Augustus, he held tribunician [power for the fourth time], was consul designate for the 5th time, imperator for the 6th time, father of the fatherland, father of the army. [---]a Prima, daughter of Publius, sacerdos of the [divine?] Drusilla (set this up).</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>If we follow the restoration, that [---] Prima held a priesthood to diva Drusilla, this priesthood is most likely to have been awarded between 38 CE (the death of Drusilla) and Jan 41 CE (the inscription of the stone). Drusilla's divinisation, attested by the Arval Acta to havebeen on 23 Sep 38 CE is a possible terminus ante quem (although they may not have waiting for her to be officially deified). However, fitting diva in the lacuna on line 5 (at least without abbreviation) would be difficult, and thus may have been a priesthood to her as a living divinity.</p> 
            </div>
